---

<html lang="en-GB">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta name="view-transition" content="same-origin" />
  <title>About Charlie Waite | Camber Co</title>
  <meta name="description" content="About Charlie Waite: London software engineer, founder of Camber Consulting, and builder of AI-driven products and systems." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=Figtree:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>

<body>
  <canvas id="lightField" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
  <div class="grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <nav class="nav" role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo"><span class="logo-text">Camber Co</span></a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/" class="nav-link">Home</a>
        <a href="#journey" class="nav-link">Journey</a>
        <a href="#projects" class="nav-link">Projects</a>
        <a href="#play" class="nav-link">Interactive</a>
      </div>
      <a href="https://calendly.com/camber-co/30min" class="nav-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Book Free Audit →</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <section class="hero" id="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy reveal">
          <p class="hero-tag">About Me</p>
          <h1 class="hero-title">Charlie Waite,<br /><em>software engineer for 12 years</em></h1>
          <p class="hero-subtitle">
            I'm based in London and founded Camber Consulting in <strong>2026</strong>.
            I started it to help businesses actually deploy AI systems, not just discuss them.
            My focus is practical architecture: agentic workflows, automation pipelines,
            and products that make teams significantly more efficient.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="#projects" class="btn btn-primary">See Projects</a>
            <a href="#play" class="btn btn-ghost">Try Interactive Mode</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-panel reveal" aria-label="Founder summary">
          <div class="terminal">
            <p><span class="prompt">$</span> founder.summary --latest</p>
            <p id="typeLine" class="type-line"></p>
            <p><span class="prompt">$</span> expertise</p>
            <p><strong>Delivery:</strong> AI systems and automation</p>
            <p><strong>Approach:</strong> Build fast, test hard, ship outcomes</p>
          </div>
          <div class="nano-art">
            <div class="ring ring-1"></div>
            <div class="ring ring-2"></div>
            <div class="ring ring-3"></div>
            <p>Nano Banana Concept Layer</p>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="journey" id="journey">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="section-tag">Journey</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Building with AI before it was standard</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline">
          <article class="timeline-item reveal">
            <span class="timeline-year">Early AI wave</span>
            <h3>AI-Based Playwright Testing</h3>
            <p>
              Brought AI-guided Playwright testing into workflows while AI was still early as a productivity tool,
              accelerating regression coverage and release confidence.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="timeline-item reveal">
            <span class="timeline-year">2026</span>
            <h3>Founded Camber Consulting</h3>
            <p>
              Launched Camber to help businesses operationalise AI with implementation-first consulting:
              architecture, automation, integration, and team enablement.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="timeline-item reveal">
            <span class="timeline-year">Current</span>
            <h3>From Zero Knowledge to App Store</h3>
            <p>
              Consulted with two solo developers with no technical background and guided each from zero knowledge
              to shipping an app on the App Store.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="projects" id="projects">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="section-tag">Selected Work</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Products and platforms</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="project-grid">
          <article class="project-card reveal" data-tilt>
            <h3>Football IQ</h3>
            <p>
              Football trivia app with daily challenge loops, multiple game modes,
              and progression-driven retention.
            </p>
            <a href="https://www.football-iq.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.football-iq.app</a>
          </article>

          <article class="project-card project-plus reveal" data-tilt>
            <h3>Plus AI Tools Suite</h3>
            <p class="project-intro">
              Grouped platform work across three Plus products, centered on AI-assisted insight,
              prediction interfaces, and high-clarity user decision flows.
            </p>

            <div class="plus-grid">
              <div class="plus-item">
                <h4>WhoScored Plus</h4>
                <p>AI-assisted football analysis and conversational insight surfaces.</p>
                <a href="https://www.whoscored.com/plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">whoscored.com/plus</a>
              </div>
              <div class="plus-item">
                <h4>Oddschecker Plus</h4>
                <p>Value and trend tooling driven by fast-changing market signals.</p>
                <a href="https://www.oddschecker.com/plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">oddschecker.com/plus</a>
              </div>
              <div class="plus-item">
                <h4>Gazzetta AI Predictor</h4>
                <p>Prediction-led football experiences built for intuitive user understanding.</p>
                <a href="https://ai.predictor.gazzetta.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ai.predictor.gazzetta.it</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="project-card reveal" data-tilt>
            <h3>AI-Native QA Systems</h3>
            <p>
              Embedded AI in browser automation and test orchestration to reduce manual QA effort,
              improve reliability, and shorten delivery cycles.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="project-card reveal" data-tilt>
            <h3>Founder Acceleration</h3>
            <p>
              Worked directly with non-technical solo founders, taking them from first principles to shipped products,
              with reusable build systems and practical AI workflows.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="play" id="play">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="section-tag">Interactive</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">AI Time Warp Estimator</h2>
          <p class="section-desc">Turn repetitive monthly tasks into an estimated time-recovered plan.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="lab-shell reveal">
          <div class="lab-column">
            <h3>Input Tasks</h3>
            <p class="lab-copy">Add repetitive tasks and monthly time spent on each.</p>
            <div id="taskRows" class="task-rows">
              <div class="task-row">
                <input class="task-name" type="text" placeholder="Task name (e.g. Weekly reporting)" maxlength="100" />
                <input class="task-hours" type="number" min="0.5" max="500" step="0.5" placeholder="Hours / month" />
                <button class="task-remove" type="button" aria-label="Remove task">x</button>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="task-actions">
              <button id="addTask" class="btn btn-ghost" type="button">Add Task</button>
              <button id="sampleTasks" class="btn btn-ghost" type="button">Load Example</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="lab-column">
            <h3>Run Estimate</h3>
            <p class="lab-copy">Model estimates realistic monthly automation gains.</p>
            <div class="lab-actions">
              <button id="runEstimate" class="btn btn-primary" type="button">Estimate Time Saved</button>
              <button id="clearTasks" class="btn btn-ghost" type="button">Clear</button>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-track" id="flowTrack" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="flow-dot"></span>
              <span class="flow-dot"></span>
              <span class="flow-dot"></span>
              <span class="flow-dot"></span>
            </div>
            <p class="estimator-note" id="estimatorNote">Tip: include monthly repetitive tasks for stronger estimates.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="lab-column output-column">
            <h3>Savings Output</h3>
            <div class="score-grid">
              <div class="score-card">
                <p>Monthly Hours</p>
                <strong id="metricMonthlySaved">0</strong>
              </div>
              <div class="score-card">
                <p>Yearly Hours</p>
                <strong id="metricYearlySaved">0</strong>
              </div>
              <div class="score-card">
                <p>Workdays / Year</p>
                <strong id="metricDaysSaved">0</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="stack-grade" id="stackGrade">Awaiting estimate...</p>
            <p class="stack-story" id="stackStory">Run a simulation to see estimated hours you can recover.</p>
            <div id="taskBreakdown" class="task-breakdown"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta reveal">
      <div class="container cta-card">
        <h2>Business-first on the homepage. Builder-first here.</h2>
        <p>
          If you want to see how this thinking applies to your company,
          Camber can design and ship your next AI workflow in production.
        </p>
        <a href="https://calendly.com/camber-co/30min" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Book a Call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p>Charlie Waite · London · Camber Consulting</p>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const typeLine = document.getElementById('typeLine');
    const phrase = '2026: founded Camber Consulting to turn AI potential into working systems.';
    let charIndex = 0;
    const typeTick = () => {
      if (!typeLine || charIndex > phrase.length) return;
      typeLine.textContent = phrase.slice(0, charIndex);
      charIndex += 1;
      setTimeout(typeTick, 20);
    };
    typeTick();

    const revealables = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
    const revealObserver = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) entry.target.classList.add('visible');
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.15, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });
    revealables.forEach((el) => revealObserver.observe(el));

    const tiltCards = document.querySelectorAll('[data-tilt]');
    tiltCards.forEach((card) => {
      card.addEventListener('mousemove', (ev) => {
        const rect = card.getBoundingClientRect();
        const x = (ev.clientX - rect.left) / rect.width;
        const y = (ev.clientY - rect.top) / rect.height;
        const ry = (x - 0.5) * 5;
        const rx = (0.5 - y) * 4;
        card.style.transform = `perspective(900px) rotateX(${rx}deg) rotateY(${ry}deg) translateY(-2px)`;
      });
      card.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
        card.style.transform = '';
      });
    });

    const taskRows = document.getElementById('taskRows');
    const addTaskBtn = document.getElementById('addTask');
    const sampleTasksBtn = document.getElementById('sampleTasks');
    const runEstimateBtn = document.getElementById('runEstimate');
    const clearTasksBtn = document.getElementById('clearTasks');
    const flowTrack = document.getElementById('flowTrack');
    const metricMonthlySaved = document.getElementById('metricMonthlySaved');
    const metricYearlySaved = document.getElementById('metricYearlySaved');
    const metricDaysSaved = document.getElementById('metricDaysSaved');
    const stackGrade = document.getElementById('stackGrade');
    const stackStory = document.getElementById('stackStory');
    const estimatorNote = document.getElementById('estimatorNote');
    const taskBreakdown = document.getElementById('taskBreakdown');

    const createTaskRow = (name = '', hours = '') => {
      const row = document.createElement('div');
      row.className = 'task-row';
      row.innerHTML = `
        <input class="task-name" type="text" placeholder="Task name (e.g. Weekly reporting)" maxlength="100" />
        <input class="task-hours" type="number" min="0.5" max="500" step="0.5" placeholder="Hours / month" />
        <button class="task-remove" type="button" aria-label="Remove task">x</button>
      `;
      row.querySelector('.task-name').value = name;
      row.querySelector('.task-hours').value = hours;
      row.querySelector('.task-remove').addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (taskRows.children.length <= 1) {
          row.querySelector('.task-name').value = '';
          row.querySelector('.task-hours').value = '';
          return;
        }
        row.remove();
      });
      return row;
    };

    taskRows?.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
      const target = event.target;
      if (!(target instanceof HTMLElement)) return;
      if (!target.classList.contains('task-remove')) return;
      const row = target.closest('.task-row');
      if (!row) return;
      if (taskRows.children.length <= 1) {
        row.querySelector('.task-name').value = '';
        row.querySelector('.task-hours').value = '';
        return;
      }
      row.remove();
    });

    const animateNumber = (element, target) => {
      const start = Number(element.textContent) || 0;
      const delta = target - start;
      const duration = 450;
      const startTime = performance.now();
      const tick = (now) => {
        const progress = Math.min(1, (now - startTime) / duration);
        element.textContent = String(Math.round((start + delta * progress) * 10) / 10);
        if (progress < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
      };
      requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    };

    const collectTasks = () => {
      return [...taskRows.querySelectorAll('.task-row')]
        .map((row) => {
          const name = row.querySelector('.task-name')?.value?.trim();
          const hours = Number(row.querySelector('.task-hours')?.value);
          return { name, hoursPerMonth: hours };
        })
        .filter((task) => task.name && Number.isFinite(task.hoursPerMonth) && task.hoursPerMonth > 0);
    };

    const setLoadingState = (loading) => {
      runEstimateBtn.disabled = loading;
      runEstimateBtn.textContent = loading ? 'Estimating...' : 'Estimate Time Saved';
      flowTrack?.classList.toggle('running', loading);
      if (loading) estimatorNote.textContent = 'Running AI estimate...';
    };

    const renderBreakdown = (tasks) => {
      if (!tasks.length) {
        taskBreakdown.innerHTML = '';
        return;
      }
      taskBreakdown.innerHTML = tasks.map((task) => {
        const width = Math.max(5, task.automationPotentialPercent);
        return `
          <div class="breakdown-item">
            <div class="breakdown-head">
              <strong>${task.name}</strong>
              <span>${task.estimatedHoursSavedPerMonth}h / mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="breakdown-bar"><span style="width:${width}%"></span></div>
          </div>
        `;
      }).join('');
    };

    const showEstimate = (payload) => {
      animateNumber(metricMonthlySaved, payload.summary.estimatedHoursSavedPerMonth);
      animateNumber(metricYearlySaved, payload.summary.estimatedHoursSavedPerYear);
      animateNumber(metricDaysSaved, payload.summary.workingDaysRecoveredPerYear);
      stackGrade.textContent = `Confidence: ${payload.summary.confidence.toUpperCase()}`;
      stackStory.textContent = payload.summary.rationale;
      estimatorNote.textContent = payload.source === 'ai'
        ? 'AI model estimate complete.'
        : 'AI key unavailable. Showing heuristic estimate.';
      renderBreakdown(payload.tasks);
      flowTrack?.classList.remove('running');
      void flowTrack?.offsetWidth;
      flowTrack?.classList.add('running');
    };

    addTaskBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      if (taskRows.children.length >= 8) return;
      taskRows.appendChild(createTaskRow());
    });

    sampleTasksBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      taskRows.innerHTML = '';
      const samples = [
        ['Weekly reporting prep', '12'],
        ['Inbox sorting and follow-up', '18'],
        ['CRM updates and admin logging', '16'],
        ['Meeting notes and summaries', '10']
      ];
      samples.forEach(([name, hours]) => taskRows.appendChild(createTaskRow(name, hours)));
    });

    clearTasksBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      taskRows.innerHTML = '';
      taskRows.appendChild(createTaskRow());
      animateNumber(metricMonthlySaved, 0);
      animateNumber(metricYearlySaved, 0);
      animateNumber(metricDaysSaved, 0);
      stackGrade.textContent = 'Awaiting estimate...';
      stackStory.textContent = 'Run a simulation to see estimated hours you can recover.';
      estimatorNote.textContent = 'Tip: include monthly repetitive tasks for stronger estimates.';
      taskBreakdown.innerHTML = '';
      flowTrack?.classList.remove('running');
    });

    runEstimateBtn?.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const tasks = collectTasks();
      if (!tasks.length) {
        stackGrade.textContent = 'Add at least one task';
        stackStory.textContent = 'Enter task names and monthly hours to run the estimate.';
        return;
      }

      setLoadingState(true);
      try {
        const response = await fetch('/api/estimate-savings', {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ tasks })
        });
        const payload = await response.json();
        if (!response.ok) {
          stackGrade.textContent = 'Estimate unavailable';
          stackStory.textContent = payload?.error || 'Could not calculate estimate.';
          setLoadingState(false);
          return;
        }
        showEstimate(payload);
      } catch {
        stackGrade.textContent = 'Network error';
        stackStory.textContent = 'Could not reach estimator endpoint.';
      } finally {
        setLoadingState(false);
      }
    });

    const lightField = document.getElementById('lightField');
    const ctx = lightField?.getContext('2d');
    const particles = [];
    let width = 0;
    let height = 0;

    const setupField = () => {
      if (!lightField) return;
      width = window.innerWidth;
      height = window.innerHeight;
      lightField.width = width;
      lightField.height = height;
      particles.length = 0;

      for (let i = 0; i < 65; i += 1) {
        particles.push({
          x: Math.random() * width,
          y: Math.random() * height,
          vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.3,
          vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.3,
          r: 1 + Math.random() * 1.8
        });
      }
    };

    const renderField = () => {
      if (!ctx) return;
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, width, height);
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.34)';

      particles.forEach((p) => {
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        if (p.x < 0 || p.x > width) p.vx *= -1;
        if (p.y < 0 || p.y > height) p.vy *= -1;

        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(p.x, p.y, p.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fill();
      });

      requestAnimationFrame(renderField);
    };

    setupField();
    renderField();
    window.addEventListener('resize', setupField);
  </script>
</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  :root {
    --bg: #ffffff;
    --surface: #f8fafc;
    --surface-2: #f1f5f9;
    --ink: #0f172a;
    --text: #334155;
    --muted: #64748b;
    --line: #e2e8f0;
    --amber: #f59e0b;
    --slate: #1e293b;
  }

  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }

  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Figtree', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    color: var(--text);
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 12% 8%, #f8fafc 0%, #ffffff 42%, #f8fafc 100%);
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  #lightField {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0.55;
  }

  .grain {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.02), rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.02));
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .nav,
  main,
  .footer {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 20;
    padding: 0 24px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
    backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .nav-inner {
    max-width: 1140px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    min-height: 72px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .nav-logo { text-decoration: none; }

  .logo-text {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 24px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 26px;
  }

  .nav-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .nav-link:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  .nav-btn {
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 9px;
    padding: 10px 18px;
  }

  .nav-btn:hover { background: var(--slate); }

  .container {
    max-width: 1140px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 116px 0 72px;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
    gap: 26px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hero-tag,
  .section-tag {
    font-size: 13px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }

  .hero-title,
  .section-title,
  .timeline-item h3,
  .project-card h3,
  .plus-item h4,
  .cta-card h2 {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5.7vw, 70px);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .hero-title em {
    color: #475569;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    margin-top: 30px;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .btn {
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 13px 24px;
    transition: all 0.24s ease;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--ink);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--slate);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
  }

  .btn-ghost {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    color: var(--muted);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--line);
  }

  .btn-ghost:hover {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-color: #cbd5e1;
  }

  .hero-panel {
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .terminal,
  .nano-art,
  .timeline-item,
  .project-card,
  .lab-shell,
  .score-card,
  .cta-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 16px;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 45px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
  }

  .terminal {
    padding: 18px;
  }

  .terminal p {
    margin: 0 0 7px;
    color: #334155;
